TextBody:
Hi Azad,

Thank you for reaching out.

Please follow the steps below:

- Go to Control Panel -> Programs And Features -> Uninstall or change a program 
- Select Endpoint Protector and click Change


- Click Next on the installation wizard, click Remove, and make sure you check the Remove database and logs option, then click on Remove

- Click on OK if the restart is required

- Click on Finish

If you continue to encounter issues after performing these steps, please let us know. We can then schedule a remote session to investigate the matter further.

Best Regards,
Iosif Muntean| Technical Support Engineer
